theorem interior_compl_closed_eq_empty_iff_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) ↔ (A : Set X) = Set.univ := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen (Aᶜ : Set X) := hA_closed.isOpen_compl
  have hIntEq : interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = (Aᶜ : Set X) := hOpen.interior_eq
  constructor
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- `Aᶜ` itself is empty.
    have hComplEmpty : (Aᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [hIntEq] using hIntEmpty
    -- Taking complements yields the desired equality.
    have h := congrArg Set.compl hComplEmpty
    simpa [compl_empty, compl_compl] using h
  · intro hA_univ
    -- From `A = univ` we get `Aᶜ = ∅`.
    have hComplEmpty : (Aᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [hA_univ, Set.compl_univ]
    -- Rewrite using `hComplEmpty`.
    simpa [hComplEmpty, hIntEq] using hIntEq

theorem compl_empty {α : Type*} :
    ((∅ : Set α)ᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set α) := by
  ext x
  simp
